52.1	Elizabeth_Gilbert	Elizabeth Gilbert	Elizabeth M. Gilbert (born July 18, 1969) is an American author, essayist, short story writer, biographer, novelist and memoirist. She is best known for her 2006 memoirs, Eat, Pray, Love, which as of December 2010, has spent 199 weeks on the New York Times Best Seller list, and was also made into a film by the same name in 2010.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Elizabeth_Gilbert_at_TED.jpg/250px-Elizabeth_Gilbert_at_TED.jpg
